https://leetcode.com/problems/combination-sum/description/

class Solution {
public:
    void helper(int idx,vector<int> ds,vector<int>& arr,int target,vector<vector<int>>& res)
    {
        if(idx<0) return;
        if(target==0)
        {
            res.push_back(ds);
            return;
        }  

        //not pick
        helper(idx-1,ds,arr,target,res);

        //pick
       
        if(arr[idx]<=target)
        {
            ds.push_back(arr[idx]);
            helper(idx,ds,arr,target-arr[idx],res);
        }
    }
    vector<vector<int>> combinationSum(vector<int>& candidates, int target) 
    {
        vector<vector<int>> res;
        vector<int> ds;
        int n=candidates.size();
        helper(n-1,ds,candidates,target,res);
        return res;
    }
};


⏱️ Time Complexity

👉 O(2^T × T)

2^T → recursion tree (target depth)
T → copying each combination
📦 Space Complexity

👉 O(T) (recursion stack)

Depth = target / smallest element
Skewed tree → worst case T
🧠 One-line memory trick

👉 “Exponential recursion × linear copy = O(2^T × T)”

🎯 Interview one-liner

Time is exponential in target → O(2^T × T), space is O(T) due to recursion depth.
